# Inventory / Marketplace MVP

Internal inventory is the **source of truth**, integrated with marketplaces (Shopee/Tokopedia
now). **Adapter-first with STUBS** so the whole pipeline runs without real provider APIs.
Per-user scoped (internal-first, multi-tenant-ready). Roadmap + locked decisions:
`docs/roadmap/inventory-mvp.md`.

## Modules & domains
- **catalog** ‚Äî Product / ProductVariant (master). Server service owns Prisma (no repository).
  Every product has ‚â•1 variant; SKU `@@unique([userId, sku])`. Variant carries `cost`/`weight`,
  `lowStockThreshold`/`alertEnabled`, and reorder planning `leadTimeDays?`/`minOrderQty?` (0 in the
  UI = unset ‚Üí null). Variants are editable: `PATCH /products/:id/variants/:variantId` ‚Üí
  `updateVariant` (create/add-variant forms stay short; advanced planning is set later via Edit).
  Stock changes go through the inventory service, NEVER by writing inventory tables from catalog.
- **inventory** ‚Äî `Inventory` (fast-read cache: available/reserved/damaged/incoming) +
  **`StockLedger` (append-only = the real source of truth, available-centric)**. Every mutation =
  1 ledger row + 1 Inventory update in ONE tx. `adjustStock` (manual, never negative). Inbound-order
  stock **lifecycle trio** (all `(tx,‚Ä¶)`, available MAY go negative): `applyOrderReserveTx`
  (available‚àí, reserved+; `ORDER_RESERVE`), `applyOrderShipTx` (reserved‚àí only, available unchanged;
  `ORDER_SHIP` delta 0), `applyOrderReleaseTx` (available+, reserved‚àí; `ORDER_RELEASE`). Reserved
  decrements clamp at 0 (+warn) for orders reserved before the lifecycle existed; on-hand = available
  + reserved. Other modules' SoT writes also funnel through here: `applyReturnRestockTx`/
  `applyReturnDamagedTx` (returns), `applyOfflineSaleTx` (POS ‚Äî available‚àí, `SALE`/`POS`),
  `adjustIncomingTx`/`applyPurchaseReceiveTx` (purchasing ‚Äî the `incomingStock` bucket). Surfaces: `getDashboard` (KPIs incl. `totalReservedUnits`); `listStockOverview` (now also the
  last movement before‚Üíafter + `lastAdjustedAt`, via a nested `take:1` ledger include); **reorder
  report** (`inventory-reorder.service` ‚Äî recency-weighted/EWMA velocity ‚Üí days-of-cover ‚Üí suggested
  qty, honours per-variant lead time/MOQ; bucketed ledger sums per sub-window); **stock activity
  log** (`inventory-activity.service` ‚Äî filter reason/source/direction/date + paginate + CSV export).
  Demand reasons for velocity are centralised in `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS` (ORDER_RESERVE + ORDER_RELEASE
  + RETURN + SALE, NOT delta-0 ORDER_SHIP ‚Äî avoids double-count; nets returns + counts offline POS
  sales). Pure `utils/stock-math.ts` + `utils/reorder-math.ts` are unit-tested.
- **marketplace** ‚Äî connections (`MarketplaceConnection`; now also `lastOrdersPulledAt`) +
  `MarketplaceProduct` (listing snapshot) + `MarketplaceProductMapping` (listing‚Üîvariant). Mapping
  is **1:1 on the listing** (`marketplaceProductId @unique`) but ONE variant MAY map to many
  listings ‚Äî cross-channel sync is by design, do NOT force 1:1. Import via STUB adapter; auto-map by
  NORMALIZED sku (`utils/sku-match.ts`, NOT edit-distance ‚Äî `‚Ä¶-M` ‚âÝ `‚Ä¶-L`); non-exact ‚Üí
  `NEEDS_REVIEW` + sync stays off (per-listing sync is a **Switch**, disabled while NEEDS_REVIEW).
  `mapByExternalRef` upserts a listing (creating its snapshot if never imported) + its mapping.
- **orders** ‚Äî **multi-store pull** `pullFromConnections(connectionIds?)` (default every active
  store; STUB adapter) ‚Üí resolve items via mapping ‚Üí advance the per-order **stock lifecycle** (each
  stage once, idempotent via `Order.inventoryAppliedAt`/`inventoryShippedAt`/`inventoryRevertedAt`):
  RESERVE on PAID, SHIP on SHIPPED/COMPLETED (consumes the reservation; an order first seen already
  shipped reserves then ships), RELEASE on CANCELLED-before-ship. CANCELLED-**after**-ship is a return,
  NOT a release (goods already left ‚Üí no credit): it auto-opens a return via the returns service
  (best-effort). Only available changes (reserve/release) propagate to OTHER channels ‚Äî excluding the
  source channel (`excludeConnectionId`); ship does not. Per-store **30s cooldown** keyed on
  `lastOrdersPulledAt` (skipped, not errored = anti-abuse). `resolveOrderItem` maps an unmapped item
  from the order page (via `mapByExternalRef`) then reserves stock for just the newly-resolved items of
  a PAID order (idempotent). Endpoints: `POST /api/v1/orders/pull`, `/orders/:id/resolve-item`. Pull
  lives on the **Orders** page (removed from marketplace detail).
- **fulfillment (Phase 5)** ‚Äî orders ‚Üî packing videos are joined by the shared **`noResi`**
  (no FK; matched **case-insensitively** ‚Äî the resi input is NOT force-uppercased, the scanner is).
  `Order.fulfilledAt` is stamped best-effort when a packing video completes (the recordings complete
  route calls `markFulfilledByResi` ‚Äî never fails the save). `findByResi` resolves the order for a resi
  (the station **pack view** shows its items via `useOrderByResiQuery`); recordings `findByResi` lists
  completed videos for a resi (order/return **evidence**, via `useRecordingsByResiQuery`). Links work
  **both ways**: order/return ‚Üí packing video, and the recording detail modal + pack view ‚Üí order.
  Services stay decoupled ‚Äî composition is at the route/page/hook layer. Endpoints:
  `GET /api/v1/orders/by-resi`, `GET /api/v1/recordings/by-resi`.
- **returns** ‚Äî RMA flow (`Return` + `ReturnItem`). A return opens (PENDING) for an order whose goods
  shipped ‚Äî auto on a detected post-ship cancellation, or manually from the order page ‚Äî then is
  processed once goods arrive: each line routed to **RESTOCK** (`applyReturnRestockTx`, available+) or
  **DAMAGED** (`applyReturnDamagedTx`, damagedStock+, delta-0 ledger), via the inventory service in one
  tx; restocks propagate to all channels. Ledger reason `RETURN`; restock nets out reorder velocity
  (`SALES_LEDGER_REASONS`). Idempotent (one return per order). Return detail links the packing video by
  `noResi` (dispute evidence). Endpoints: `GET/POST /api/v1/returns`, `/returns/:id`,
  `/returns/:id/process`, `/returns/:id/reject`.
- **sales (offline / POS)** ‚Äî `Sale` + `SaleItem` (snapshot sku/name/unitPrice), `SalePaymentMethod`
  (CASH/QRIS/TRANSFER), `SaleStatus` (COMPLETED/VOID), code `S00001` per-user. A counter sale
  **decrements the SoT immediately**: one tx creates the sale + lines and calls `applyOfflineSaleTx`
  per line (`available‚àí`, ledger `SALE` / source `POS` / ref = saleId, `note: 'Offline sale'`). Oversell
  is **allowed** (goods are in hand ‚Üí available MAY go negative). After commit, propagate each sold
  variant's new available to **all** sync-ready channels (selling in-store can't oversell online). The
  POS picker reads ProductVariant read-only (`searchSellableVariants`, active only, by sku/name + price +
  available). `SALE` joins `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS`, so offline sales feed reorder velocity. Endpoints:
  `GET/POST /api/v1/sales`, `/sales/:id`, `/sales/variants?q=`.
- **purchasing (restock / POs)** ‚Äî `PurchaseOrder` + `PurchaseOrderItem` (snapshot sku/name + `quantity`/
  `receivedQuantity`/`unitCost`), `PurchaseOrderStatus` ORDERED‚ÜíPARTIALLY_RECEIVED‚ÜíRECEIVED/CANCELLED,
  code `PO00001` per-user. **Lights up the `incomingStock` bucket** (the last empty one). Two inventory
  tx-methods (no over-credit): `adjustIncomingTx(tx,{variantId,delta})` ‚Äî `incomingStock += delta`
  clamped at 0, **NO ledger row** (forecast bucket, available unchanged); `applyPurchaseReceiveTx` ‚Äî
  `incoming‚àí` (clamped) + `available+`, ledger `RESTOCK` / source `PURCHASE` / ref = PO id. Lifecycle:
  **create** (already ORDERED) ‚Üí `adjustIncomingTx(+qty)` per line + `totalCost`; **receive** (only
  ORDERED/PARTIALLY_RECEIVED, per-line qty clamped to outstanding) ‚Üí `receivedQuantity +=` +
  `applyPurchaseReceiveTx`, recompute status (all received ‚Üí RECEIVED + `receivedAt`, else
  PARTIALLY_RECEIVED), propagate received variants to **all** channels; **cancel** (not-yet-RECEIVED) ‚Üí
  `adjustIncomingTx(‚àíoutstanding)` per line, status CANCELLED (already-received units stay in available).
  `supplierName` is **free text** (no Supplier entity yet); variant `cost` stays manual. `searchVariants`
  reads ProductVariant read-only (cost + available + incoming). The reorder report's **"Create PO"**
  prefills `/dashboard/purchasing/new` from URGENT/SOON suggestions. Endpoints:
  `GET/POST /api/v1/purchase-orders`, `/purchase-orders/:id`, `/:id/receive`, `/:id/cancel`,
  `/purchase-orders/variants?q=`.

## Outbound sync engine (worker-side) ‚Äî `packages/queue/src/marketplace-sync/`
SoT change ‚Üí `enqueuePropagateInventoryStock` (web, best-effort, only if `syncEnabled` mappings
exist) ‚Üí `propagate-inventory-stock` job (fan-out, idempotent per ledger event) ‚Üí
`sync-marketplace-stock` job ‚Üí `executeStockSync` (per-provider rate-limit, push LATEST
available via the provider adapter; `Dev` stub simulates success, `Unwired` stub rejects) ‚Üí
marks `MarketplaceSyncJob` + mapping `lastSyncStatus` + listing snapshot. Retryable failures
throw so BullMQ retries.

## Cross-module composition (respect boundary ¬ß3)
- catalog‚Üíinventory ONLY via the inventory service (no cross-table writes). orders‚Üíinventory via
  the lifecycle trio (`applyOrderReserveTx`/`ShipTx`/`ReleaseTx`); orders‚Üíreturns via its service
  (auto-open). returns‚Üíinventory via `applyReturnRestockTx`/`DamagedTx` and reads Order/OrderItem
  read-only. sales‚Üíinventory via `applyOfflineSaleTx`; purchasing‚Üíinventory via `adjustIncomingTx`/
  `applyPurchaseReceiveTx` ‚Äî both read ProductVariant read-only for their pickers and propagate to
  ALL channels after commit (a counter sale or restock moves sellable everywhere). A module may import
  another module's HOOKS/types but NOT its components ‚Äî cross-module UI composition lives at the APP
  layer (e.g. `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/products/[id]/product-detail-view.tsx` wires catalog
  `ProductDetail` + inventory `AdjustStockDialog`; the reorder report's "Create PO" links into
  purchasing). The variant picker reuses inventory `useStockOverviewQuery`.

## Gotchas (learned the hard way)
- **BullMQ custom jobId CANNOT contain `:`** ‚Üí job-id builders use `-` (DB idempotency keys keep `:`).
- A real provider adapter needs the **DECRYPTED token** ‚Üí lift marketplace token-crypto into a
  shared `@olshop/*` package (the engine passes the encrypted token; stubs ignore it).
- A running dev server (`tsx watch server.ts`) holds the Prisma query-engine DLL on Windows ‚Üí
  `prisma generate` fails `EPERM`. Stop it before generate/migrate; restart after. BUT an
  index-only / no-client-change migration can run with `prisma migrate dev --skip-generate`
  WITHOUT stopping the dev server (only `generate` overwrites the locked DLL).
- `next build` intermittently fails `Failed to collect page data for /<page>` while node procs
  run (a `.next` file-lock flake) ‚Äî just re-run; not a code error.
- `server-only` services can't be imported into a worker-context `tsx` script without
  `node --conditions=react-server` + the web tsconfig.
- Typed routes: after adding a new `app/**/page.tsx`, `pnpm typecheck` (`tsc`) fails on `Route`
  literals until `next build` regenerates `.next/types`. Build first, then typecheck.

## Next up ‚Äî QR-scan (POS phase 2)
The queued follow-up to POS. **Phase A (standalone): per-SKU QR/barcode labels** ‚Äî a printable label
sheet encoding the existing `ProductVariant.barcode`/`sku` (NO schema change; barcode already exists).
**Phase B: mobile scan-to-cart** ‚Äî pair a phone camera to the POS terminal to add lines by scan, REUSING
the **`scanner-pairing`** module (HARD CONSTRAINT #4 ‚Äî do NOT rename/repurpose its socket event
contracts). Phase B depends on the realtime **socket host** (custom `server.ts`, feature-gated / NOT on
Vercel ‚Äî see the deploy plan), so ship phase A (labels) first. Roadmap ¬ß10.

